Change History

Revision Date Notes
7.0.0 2021-09-28 Added Core7 service to meet the password requirements for IMDA certification. Includes the following new actions:
  • SetAdminPassword3
  • CheckAdminPassword3
  • GetAdminPasswordAuthStatus
6.0.0 2019-07-17 Added Core6 service to indicate the following actions now require authentication:
  • GetAdminPasswordRestrictions
  • GetDataUploadUserConsent
5.0.1 2017-04-11 Once disabled, SetUnsecuredWiFiWarning can no longer be enabled. Otherwise, it will return "ErrorCannotEnableUnsecuredWiFiWarning".
5.0.0 2017-02-27 Added Core5 service with new action IsServiceSupported.
4.0.0 2016-01-06 Added Core4 service to support diagnostics data uploads.

Introduced:
  • action GetDataUploadUserConsent
  • action SetDataUploadUserConsent
3.0.0 2015-07-29 Added Core3 service to support Admin password hint.

Introduced:
  • action SetAdminPassword2
  • action GetAdminPasswordHint
2.0.0 2012-11-14 Added Core2 service with action CheckAdminPassword2.

1.0.0 2012 Initial release

CheckAdminPassword

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/CheckAdminPassword
This action checks the device's admin password.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/CheckAdminPasswordResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorCannotAuthenticateWithSessionToken A session token was specified with the request. In order to check the admin password, no session token must be specified.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/core/CheckAdminPassword"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK"
}

CheckAdminPassword3

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/CheckAdminPassword3
This action checks the admin user's password, in accordance with the IMDA requirements.

Note:

This action does not require HTTP basic authentication.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
adminPassword string no The admin password to verify.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isPasswordValid bool no Whether the input password is valid.
attemptsRemaining int yes The number of consecutive failed attempts remaining, until a lockout goes into effect. This parameter will exist only if result is either ErrorInvalidAdminPassword or ErrorPasswordCheckDelayed.
delayTimeRemaining int yes The time remaining in the current delay period (seconds), after which the next password check can be attempted. This parameter will exist only if result is either ErrorInvalidAdminPassword or ErrorPasswordCheckDelayed.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/CheckAdminPassword3Result
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorAdminAccountLocked The number of consecutive failed attempts has reached the limit, so the admin account is locked.
ErrorInvalidAdminPassword The specified password is not valid.
ErrorPasswordCheckDelayed The password check function is currently delayed, as the result of a previous password failure. The next check cannot be executed until delayExpirationTime.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/core/CheckAdminPassword3"

{
  "adminPassword": "let#Me#IN01!"
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "isPasswordValid": true
  }
}

GetAdminPasswordAuthStatus

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetAdminPasswordAuthStatus
This action gets the status of admin password authentication attempts executed by CheckAdminPassword3.

Note:

This action does not require HTTP basic authentication.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
attemptsRemaining int no The number of consecutive failed attempts remaining, until a lockout goes into effect. A value of 0 indicates that the admin accout has been locked, due to excessive failed attempts.
delayTimeRemaining int yes The time remaining (seconds) in the current delay period for password authentication. This parameter will be present only if a delay is currently in effect, due to a previous password failure.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetAdminPasswordAuthStatusResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetAdminPasswordAuthStatus"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "attemptsRemaining": 3,
    "delayTimeRemaining": 23
  }
}

GetAdminPasswordRestrictions

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetAdminPasswordRestrictions
This action gets the restrictions that the device imposes on its admin password.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
minLength int no The minimum length of the admin password, in bytes.
maxLength int no The maximum length of the admin password, in bytes.
allowedCharacters UnicodeRange[] no A list of Unicode codepoint ranges, the union of which represents the complete set of characters that are allowed in the admin password. This array will always contain at least one item.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetAdminPasswordRestrictionsResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetAdminPasswordRestrictions"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "minLength": 8,
    "maxLength": 16,
    "allowedCharacters": [
      {
        "lowCodepoint": 32,
        "highCodepoint": 126
      }
    ]
  }
}

GetDeviceInfo

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetDeviceInfo
This service provides access to basic device properties and settings. This action returns basic information about the device. Any device that exposes a JNAP server must implement this action.

Note:

This action does not require HTTP basic authentication.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
manufacturer string no The manufacturer of the device.
modelNumber string no The model number of the device.
hardwareVersion string no The hardware version of the device.
description string no A brief description of the device.
serialNumber string no The serial number of the device.
firmwareVersion string no The version number of the device's firmware.
firmwareDate DateTime no The date and time associated with the device's firmware.
services string[] no The JNAP services exposed by the device.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/GetDeviceInfoResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

}

{

SetAdminPassword2

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetAdminPassword2
This action sets the device's admin password and the optional password hint. This action will set isAdminPasswordSetByUser to true.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
adminPassword string no The new admin password of the device. Devices may restrict the length and content of their admin password as they see fit. Clients can invoke the GetAdminPasswordRestrictions action to determine the specific restrictions imposed by the device.
passwordHint string yes An optional hint for the admin password. This is a word or phrase that can be used as a reminder to the user of what the password is. The maximum length of this value is 512 bytes.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetAdminPassword2Result
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorInvalidAdminPassword The specified admin password is not valid for this device.
ErrorInvalidPasswordHint The specified password hint is not valid.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetAdminPassword2"

{
  "adminPassword": "letmeIN!",
  "passwordHint": "This is the hint!"

HTTP/1.1 200 OK

SetAdminPassword3

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetAdminPassword3
This action sets the device's admin password and the optional password hint, in accordance with the IMDA requirements. This action will set isAdminPasswordSetByUser to true.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
adminPassword string no The new admin password of the device. The length and content of the password must conform to the IMDA security requirements.
passwordHint string yes An optional hint for the admin password. This is a word or phrase that can be used as a reminder to the user of what the password is. The maximum length of this value is 512 bytes.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetAdminPassword3Result

SetUnsecuredWiFiWarning

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetUnsecuredWiFiWarning
This action sets the router's unsecured wifi warning state.

Note:

This action does not require HTTP basic authentication.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
enabled bool no Whether or not to enable the unsecured wifi warning is enabled. If true, the router will present a blocking page when the Internet is accessed. If false, access to the Internet will not be blocked. Once it is disabled, it cannot be re-enabled.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/core/SetUnsecuredWiFiWarningResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorCannotEnableUnsecuredWiFiWarning The unsecured wifi warning cannot be enabled.
